 :tx/rationale "Create task: TSV-2 (REVISED): OutputMode::Tsv + json_to_tsv render-time conversion via ACP pipeline (INV-INTERFACE-001, INV-BUDGET-007). BACKGROUND: Original TSV-2 proposed adding tsv: String to CommandOutput — WRONG. TSV is a RENDERING concern computed at render time from the existing JSON/ACP structure, not a parallel data field. The JSON already contains all structured data. TSV = flatten JSON object/array to rows+columns at render time. APPROACH: (1) Add OutputMode::Tsv variant with Display/FromStr ('tsv'). (2) Add json_to_tsv(json: &Value, spec: &TsvSpec) -> String kernel utility. TsvSpec = { fields: Vec<(key_path, header_name)>, array_path: Option<String> }. For objects: one row per key-value. For arrays of objects: header row + one row per element. (3) Per-command TsvSpec constants: TASK_LIST_TSV = { array_path: 'tasks', fields: [('id','id'), ('priority','P'), ('type','type'), ('status','status'), ('title','title')] }. STATUS_TSV = { array_path: None, fields: auto-from-keys }. (4) In output.rs render(): OutputMode::Tsv => json_to_tsv(&self.json, &infer_tsv_spec(&self.json)). (5) Budget gate bypasses Tsv (like Json). (6) CRITICAL: Uses same ACP _acp JSON structure — TSV renders the ACP action + context blocks as rows when _acp present. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Zero changes to CommandOutput struct. (B) braid task list --format tsv produces correct TSV from existing JSON. (C) braid status --format tsv produces key-value rows from ACP JSON. (D) Budget gate bypasses TSV. (E) json_to_tsv is a pure function (no IO, no store access). DEPENDS-ON: TSV-1. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/budget.rs (json_to_tsv) + crates/braid/src/output.rs (OutputMode + render)"
